Program: Discovery
Title: Global population
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxj6
Last Broadcast Date: 22 October 1999
The increasing problem of global population rise. By 2025 the United Nations estimates the world's population will top eight billion people. For some the figures are a concern but for others they are proof that infant mortality is reducing and advances in medicine are working. A panel examines the challenges a larger world population will produce. Show less